    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect signaling procedure sequence in UE initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe UE initialization sequence in lte-uesoftmodem has an incorrect order of operations that causes RRC initialization to occur before UE threads are fully ready. This leads to race conditions where RRC messages may be sent to threads that haven't completed their initialization, resulting in dropped messages and failed RRC connections.\n\nThe issue manifests as failed RRC connections during UE attach procedures, with RRC messages not being properly processed by the UE layers. In some cases, this can cause the UE to get stuck in RRC_IDLE state indefinitely.\n\nThe root cause is that dl_phy_sync_success() is called before the thread synchronization signal is sent, meaning RRC initialization happens prematurely before all UE threads are ready to handle RRC messages.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-uesoftmodem.c`: Moved dl_phy_sync_success() call to occur after thread synchronization signal is sent, ensuring all UE threads are properly initialized before RRC initialization begins.\n"
}